.help gemlist November2011 gemini.gemtools
.ih
NAME
gemlist -- Generate a list of file names in standard Gemini format
.ih
USAGE
gemlist root range
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls root
The date/instrument part of the file name (everything up to the
per-night index, typically ending in "S").
.le
.ls range
A range specification (see "help ranges") for the file name indices.
.le
.ih 
DESCRIPTION

The GEMLIST task is used to expand a root name and index range to
provide a list of file names for processing.

Gemini packages typically provide an output prefix by default, so a
convenient way of reducing data is to list related images (object,
arc, flats etc) in separate files using GEMLIST and then use the
@-expansion feature of the IRAF CL to process those files.
.ih
EXAMPLES

1. Here three object files are passed to NSPREPARE.  That task, by
default, prepends the character "n" the the file names for output.  So
the same list, with an "n" prefix, is used to stack the prepared data.

.nf
    cl> gemlist S20040307S 1-3 > obj
    cl> type obj
    S20040307S0001
    S20040307S0002
    S20040307S0003
    cl> nsprepare @obj
    ...
    cl> nsstack n@obj
.fi

2. Some examples of the range syntax.  See "help ranges" for more
details.

.nf
    cl> gemlist S20040307S 1-4x2
    S20040307S0001
    S20040307S0003
    cl> gemlist S20040307S 10-11,13
    S20040307S0010
    S20040307S0011
    S20040307S0013
.fi
.endhelp
